{\an5}<i>♪ Teenage Mutant</i>
<i>Ninja Turtles ♪</i>

00:25.792 --> 00:28.461
<i>♪ Heroes in the half-shell</i>
<i>Turtle power ♪</i>

00:28.528 --> 00:30.730
{\an8}<i>♪ Rise ♪</i>

00:30.797 --> 00:32.899
[squeaking]

00:32.966 --> 00:34.567
- All alone.

00:34.634 --> 00:36.636
Where are my brothers?
They said they'd be here.

00:36.703 --> 00:38.671
[groaning]

00:38.738 --> 00:41.474
<i>[jazzy music]</i>

00:41.541 --> 00:46.179
{\an9}- Uh oh, Donnie forgot to
text Raph we were running late.

00:46.246 --> 00:48.314
{\an8}- Oh, sweet, sweet Angelo,

00:48.381 --> 00:50.784
{\an8}how soon you forget
that today, I am on vacation.

00:50.850 --> 00:54.154
{\an8}Hence, my board shorts:
The international sign for

00:54.220 --> 00:55.922
{\an8}"I am not a
useful member of society."

00:55.989 --> 00:58.224
{\an1}- We only left the guy alone
for five minutes.

00:58.291 --> 01:00.560
And we told him
we had to find tubes.

01:00.627 --> 01:03.963
- This is a job
for Dr. Delicate Touch.

01:04.030 --> 01:05.765
[clears throat]

01:05.832 --> 01:07.534
Get your mind right, son!

01:07.600 --> 01:09.803
{\an1}- [yelps]

01:09.869 --> 01:11.438
<i>[rock music]</i>

01:11.504 --> 01:13.072
- [laughs]

01:14.741 --> 01:16.209
- What took so long?

01:16.276 --> 01:19.112
{\an1}You know Raph gets weird
when I'm left alone.

01:19.179 --> 01:21.581
{\an1}- Relax.
Did you get a tube?

01:21.648 --> 01:24.117
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

01:24.184 --> 01:27.420
both: Whoa!
- Where did you get that?

01:27.487 --> 01:28.655
- Uh...

01:28.721 --> 01:30.390
[metal creaks]

01:32.258 --> 01:34.794
Borrowed it from Splinter?

01:34.861 --> 01:39.466
- Splinter, who only owns robes
and a shady past, let you--

01:41.701 --> 01:42.869
- Tube time!

01:42.936 --> 01:44.170
[laughs]

01:44.237 --> 01:46.072
- Okay men, New York's sewers

01:46.139 --> 01:48.107
are a dangerous
and complex labyrinth--

01:48.174 --> 01:50.343
- Full of creatures
and games and rides?

01:50.410 --> 01:53.246
This is going to be amazing!
- What, no.

01:53.313 --> 01:55.615
Where do you think we are?
Just take every left turn

01:55.682 --> 01:57.283
{\an3}to stay on
the lazy river,<i> capisce?</i>

01:57.350 --> 02:01.087
- Whatever, Donnie.
Mad Dogs, ahoy!

02:01.154 --> 02:04.090
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

02:04.157 --> 02:06.125
- Ain't this the life, boys?

02:06.192 --> 02:08.026
A day off
from Splinter's training

02:08.094 --> 02:10.163
to kick back
and bask in the luxury of--

02:10.229 --> 02:11.731
- Dunk-a-roo!

02:11.798 --> 02:13.333
[all yelp]

02:13.399 --> 02:14.534
[gasping]

02:14.601 --> 02:15.535
[coughing]

02:15.602 --> 02:16.736
{\an3}- [groans]

02:16.803 --> 02:18.538
{\an3}Can't you guys
just do a sports pass

02:18.605 --> 02:20.440
{\an3}with your smelly ball
or something?

02:20.507 --> 02:23.042
- Who you calling smelly?
Lace Face has been

02:23.109 --> 02:25.078
part of this family
longer than you.

02:25.144 --> 02:28.214
Now, let's run
the Midnight Special, boys

02:28.281 --> 02:30.517
- Look alive, Leo!

02:30.583 --> 02:31.918
- [laughs]

02:31.985 --> 02:34.521
And trick passing.

02:34.587 --> 02:36.623
<i>[rock music]</i>

02:36.689 --> 02:38.057
- Sports!

02:38.124 --> 02:41.728
- I got it, I got it!
Oh, yeah!

02:41.794 --> 02:43.796
[cheering]

02:43.863 --> 02:45.832
- Yeah!

02:45.899 --> 02:48.201
Uh-oh.

02:48.268 --> 02:51.638
- Our football!
Oh, and Raph!

02:51.704 --> 02:52.906
[all groaning]

02:52.972 --> 02:55.375
- Wrong way!

02:55.441 --> 03:00.346
all: Raph, whee!
Raph, whee!

03:00.413 --> 03:03.917
{\an1}- Guys!
Don't leave me alone!

03:03.983 --> 03:05.985
- We will find you, Raph!

03:06.052 --> 03:07.820
[all yelling]

03:10.323 --> 03:12.692
- Raph is all alone!
Guys, we need to--

03:12.759 --> 03:14.727
- Go down that slide again?
- Yes, agreed.

03:14.794 --> 03:16.496
Raph'll make it home
eventually, I'm sure.

03:16.563 --> 03:18.898
- No, Raph's our brother, and--
- Then why doesn't

03:18.965 --> 03:22.502
he have Splinter's
rugged good looks like we do?

03:22.569 --> 03:23.970
[grunts]

03:24.037 --> 03:25.438
<i>[soft music]</i>

03:25.505 --> 03:27.574
{\an3}- You know how savage Raph gets
when he's alone.

03:27.640 --> 03:29.776
{\an3}He'll totally lose it
if we don't find him fast.

03:29.842 --> 03:31.544
Clock's ticking.
- Fine.

03:31.611 --> 03:33.947
{\an1}But just so we're clear,
today is my day off.

03:34.013 --> 03:37.083
Respect the board shorts, bros.
- Okay, cool.

03:37.150 --> 03:40.420
{\an3}Now, we need to go back up that
tunnel to where we lost him.

03:40.486 --> 03:42.221
- You guys got to try this.

03:42.288 --> 03:44.691
[sharp inhale]

03:44.757 --> 03:45.925
[loud clangs]

03:45.992 --> 03:47.760
- [yells]

03:49.729 --> 03:51.130
Tire and Lace Face,

03:51.197 --> 03:53.900
we just need to
pull ourselves up and--

03:53.967 --> 03:56.336
<i>[low beeping]</i>

03:56.402 --> 04:01.007
Tire, Lace Face!
My emotional crutches!

04:01.074 --> 04:04.210
[grunts]

04:04.277 --> 04:05.979
Okay, Raph,
you're a little lost,

04:06.045 --> 04:09.015
a bit scared, and very alone.

04:09.082 --> 04:11.217
[heavy breathing]

04:13.519 --> 04:15.321
[exhales]

04:16.356 --> 04:18.423
Time to panic!

04:18.491 --> 04:20.093
I'm alone and panicking,

04:20.159 --> 04:22.595
panicking,
panicking, panicking!

04:22.662 --> 04:26.199
Oof, glad I kept that part
under control.

04:29.869 --> 04:31.070
Whoopsie-daisy.

04:31.137 --> 04:33.039
[metal creaking]

04:33.106 --> 04:35.775
{\an3}- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
You guys hear that?

04:35.842 --> 04:37.744
- [yelling]

04:37.810 --> 04:38.945
[all groaning]

04:39.012 --> 04:42.582
- Ow, my brain!
Ow, my other brain!

04:42.649 --> 04:45.451
- Huh, guys?
Is that you?

04:45.518 --> 04:48.621
Where are you?
Don't lose it, Raph.

04:48.688 --> 04:49.889
[exhales]

04:49.956 --> 04:51.124
Please.

04:51.190 --> 04:55.228
{\an3}- Hey Ben, look.
It's that red guy.

04:55.294 --> 04:57.797
- Oh, he's one of
those turtle jerks

04:57.864 --> 05:00.433
{\an1}that we hate, you know,
for reasons I can't remember.

05:00.500 --> 05:02.368
Let's eat him!
- [groans]

05:02.435 --> 05:04.804
{\an3}Do you know how much trouble
turtle is to eat?

05:04.871 --> 05:08.441
You got to crack the shell,
you got to drain the goo,

05:08.508 --> 05:10.243
you got to scoop out
the eyeballs

05:10.309 --> 05:12.311
so he can't
see you eating them.

05:12.378 --> 05:15.181
Plus, it's not even
that much meat.

05:15.248 --> 05:17.316
No thanks.
Hard pass.

05:17.383 --> 05:19.519
{\an1}- Okay, what if I told you
there's a shortcut?

05:19.585 --> 05:21.120
I heard if you scare them,

05:21.187 --> 05:22.922
they just pop right
out of their shell.

05:22.989 --> 05:25.258
{\an3}- And they just what, like,
jump into your belly?

05:25.324 --> 05:27.527
{\an1}- Yes!
Well, uh, actually,

05:27.593 --> 05:30.463
{\an1}full disclosure, I don't know.
But let's find out!

05:30.530 --> 05:32.999
[both groaning]

05:33.066 --> 05:34.967
<i>[bright music]</i>

05:35.034 --> 05:36.169
[slurping]

05:36.235 --> 05:38.571
- Uh, where did you get that?

05:38.638 --> 05:40.606
{\an3}- Today's vibes
were supposed to be chill,

05:40.673 --> 05:41.974
so I went ahead and filled

05:42.041 --> 05:43.776
my Battle Shell
with some refreshment.

05:43.843 --> 05:46.846
- Just one, Donald?
- And ice.

05:46.913 --> 05:48.347
I'm not an animal.

05:48.414 --> 05:51.984
{\an1}- Then give us ice for our
horribly mangled bodies.

05:52.051 --> 05:53.686
<i>[mechanical whirring]</i>

05:53.753 --> 05:54.887
- It melted.

05:54.954 --> 05:56.089
[slurping]

05:56.155 --> 05:57.657
Mmm, perfect.

05:57.724 --> 06:00.126
{\an3}- Guys, I think something
horrible happened here!

06:00.193 --> 06:03.129
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

06:03.196 --> 06:05.431
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:05.498 --> 06:08.267
- Respect the shorts, please.
It is my day off.

06:08.334 --> 06:10.470
But if I was able to do
some analysis,

06:10.536 --> 06:11.971
I'd tell you that--
- Raph was here.

06:12.038 --> 06:15.341
{\an3}- Let's not jump to
conclusions there, Leon.

06:15.408 --> 06:18.578
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

06:18.644 --> 06:21.180
{\an1}- Maybe this Raph's
seen our Raph.

06:21.247 --> 06:22.682
- We'd better hurry.

06:22.749 --> 06:26.185
- Alone, stay sharp.
Must find my--

06:26.252 --> 06:31.691
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:31.758 --> 06:33.226
[both laugh]

06:33.292 --> 06:36.429
- Ah, sewer monsters!

06:36.496 --> 06:40.333
- Yeah, we're sewer monsters!

06:40.399 --> 06:42.802
{\an3}- And we're going to
pop you out of that shell

06:42.869 --> 06:46.672
{\an3}and eat you whole,
from face to toenails!

06:46.739 --> 06:52.445
{\an1}- And you'll live in our
monster bellies alone forever!

06:52.512 --> 06:54.981
- Raph, forever alone?

06:55.047 --> 06:57.283
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

06:57.350 --> 06:59.418
[roars]

06:59.485 --> 07:01.454
[both grunting]

07:03.990 --> 07:06.225
- [heavy grunting]

07:06.292 --> 07:09.028
Savage Raph
hunt sewer monsters!

07:09.095 --> 07:10.329
[both yell]

07:10.396 --> 07:14.934
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:15.001 --> 07:16.202
- Make him stop!

07:16.269 --> 07:18.504
I'm not as tough
as I pretend to be!

07:20.573 --> 07:23.476
- Someone could get
really hurt on this.

07:23.543 --> 07:26.445
Let's see how far it swings!

07:26.512 --> 07:29.582
{\an1}- Chill, I think
I found something.

07:29.649 --> 07:32.385
- Once again, I'd love
to help bail us all out

07:32.451 --> 07:35.054
with my undeniable and
prodigious genius, but--

07:35.121 --> 07:37.423
- It was Raph.
Look.

07:37.490 --> 07:41.194
{\an3}- That's Donnie's tire.
I mean, Raph's tube.

07:41.260 --> 07:42.895
{\an1}- Uh, right.
Well, Leo,

07:42.962 --> 07:44.463
since you sell
the fewest action figures,

07:44.530 --> 07:45.731
why don't you go ahead
and jump first?

07:45.798 --> 07:47.934
{\an1}- Ignoring that.
Raph's lost because

07:48.000 --> 07:50.570
your bad pass ruined
the Midnight Special.

07:50.636 --> 07:53.806
{\an1}- Leo, chill.
We can't freak out.

07:53.873 --> 07:57.443
Nobody freak out.
Stop freaking out, Donnie!

07:57.510 --> 07:59.245
[metal rattling]

07:59.312 --> 08:00.546
[all yelling]

08:00.613 --> 08:03.149
- Make a human shield
around me!

08:03.216 --> 08:04.784
[all grunting]

08:06.786 --> 08:09.188
- Ew, gross!

08:09.255 --> 08:11.157
- Guys, we found him!
Look!

08:11.224 --> 08:15.328
- Thousand percent, not Raph.
Staking my life on it, shorts.

08:15.394 --> 08:19.599
- Raph alone!

08:19.665 --> 08:22.168
{\an3}- It might be Raph, but who--
who's to say anymore?

08:22.235 --> 08:23.736
- [grunts]

08:23.803 --> 08:26.639
This stuff is really caked on.

08:26.706 --> 08:29.842
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

08:29.909 --> 08:32.410
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:32.477 --> 08:35.014
- Lemon?
- Oh, it burns!

08:35.081 --> 08:37.582
Oh, it's in my eye stalks!

08:37.650 --> 08:40.352
- Raph, we found you!
You have no idea how--

08:40.419 --> 08:42.889
are you barbecuing villains?

08:42.955 --> 08:44.222
- [grunts]

08:44.290 --> 08:46.792
More sewer monsters?

08:46.859 --> 08:49.195
both: Huh?
- I'm sorry, sewer monsters?

08:49.262 --> 08:52.431
{\an3}Raph, hey, you are harshing
the rescue vibes, my man.

08:52.498 --> 08:54.600
It's us, okay?
Your brothers.

08:54.667 --> 08:57.970
- No brothers.
Savage Raph alone!

08:58.037 --> 08:59.572
[grunting]

08:59.639 --> 09:00.773
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:00.840 --> 09:03.342
- We're here to bring you home.

09:03.409 --> 09:08.114
- Sewer monsters invade!
Must squash!

09:08.180 --> 09:10.016
[grunting]

09:11.784 --> 09:13.219
- Okay, I want
off this ride now.

09:13.286 --> 09:15.254
Snap out of it, Raph.

09:15.321 --> 09:16.622
- Squash you!

09:16.689 --> 09:18.157
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

09:18.224 --> 09:19.792
- He still can't tell it's us.

09:19.859 --> 09:22.295
{\an1}But if we get
this sewer sludge off--

09:22.361 --> 09:24.463
Mikey, open that flood valve!

09:24.530 --> 09:25.932
- Hm...

09:25.998 --> 09:28.200
[grunting]

09:28.267 --> 09:31.037
Hm, need something stronger.

09:31.103 --> 09:33.706
both: Use Raph, use Raph,
use Raph!

09:33.773 --> 09:35.775
- No one's going to
shout the answer at me

09:35.841 --> 09:37.643
and make all
my problems disappear.

09:37.710 --> 09:40.279
Time for a little razzmatazz.

09:40.346 --> 09:41.580
- [grunts]

09:41.647 --> 09:45.051
{\an3}- Raph, I'm a nasty
sewer monster.

09:45.117 --> 09:47.954
{\an3}Don't you want to
come squash me?

09:48.020 --> 09:50.222
[grunting]

09:50.289 --> 09:51.891
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

09:54.327 --> 09:56.762
- So long, jerks!

09:57.630 --> 09:59.598
[all gasp]

09:59.665 --> 10:01.734
- Wait, where's Raph?

10:01.801 --> 10:03.869
Board shorts were my undoing!

10:03.936 --> 10:08.240
- Clean sewer monsters
still sewer monsters!

10:08.307 --> 10:11.043
Savage Raph destroy!

10:11.110 --> 10:13.512
- [yells]

10:13.579 --> 10:14.981
- Lace Face.

10:15.047 --> 10:18.184
Guys, I know how we can get
our brother back.

10:18.250 --> 10:20.353
The Midnight Special!

10:20.419 --> 10:22.054
<i>[rock music]</i>

10:22.121 --> 10:23.356
- Huh?

10:23.422 --> 10:26.092
- Look alive, Leo!

10:26.158 --> 10:27.093
- [laughs]

10:27.159 --> 10:30.062
And trick passing!

10:30.129 --> 10:32.398
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:32.465 --> 10:34.200
- Sports!

10:34.266 --> 10:35.801
- No!

10:35.868 --> 10:37.169
[grunts]

10:37.236 --> 10:40.172
[laughs]

10:40.239 --> 10:41.507
Yo, did y'all see that?

10:41.574 --> 10:44.010
- Raph!
- You're back, baby!

10:44.076 --> 10:47.446
- Back?
Uh-oh, did I get weird again?

10:47.513 --> 10:50.950
{\an1}- Super weird,
even by my standards.

10:51.017 --> 10:53.586
{\an3}- But we learned
a valuable something

10:53.652 --> 10:56.789
{\an3}about never something-ing
you alone again.

10:56.856 --> 10:59.058
- Aw, I love you guys.

10:59.125 --> 11:01.727
Now let's go home
and try tubing again tomorrow.

11:01.794 --> 11:04.730
<i>[relaxing music]</i>

11:04.797 --> 11:07.433
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:07.500 --> 11:09.635
<i>[metal clangs]</i>

11:10.603 --> 11:13.039
- Raph!

11:15.441 --> 11:20.246
<i>- Birthdays ruined.</i>
<i>Parks destroyed.</i>

11:20.312 --> 11:23.249
<i>Museums vandalized.</i>

11:23.315 --> 11:27.553
<i>Tonight on Cybersleuth,</i>
<i>I reveal the culprits.</i>

11:27.620 --> 11:31.157
<i>Beware the Mutant Menace!</i>

11:31.223 --> 11:33.125
- Mutant Menace!
Ohmigosh!

11:33.192 --> 11:34.760
They're talking about us!

11:34.827 --> 11:36.862
{\an3}- I can't believe
we're getting blamed for this!

11:36.929 --> 11:40.299
{\an9}Virtually everything in there
was somebody else's fault.

11:40.366 --> 11:41.600
{\an9}I think.

11:41.667 --> 11:43.903
{\an9}- So unfair.
Although it is a boost

11:43.969 --> 11:46.338
{\an9}for my emotionally
unavailable bad boy image.

11:46.405 --> 11:48.007
"Y'ello."
- Look, guys.

11:48.074 --> 11:49.809
{\an1}- I think this
might be an opportunity

11:49.875 --> 11:52.011
to turn a dark cloud
into a silver lining.

11:52.078 --> 11:55.281
You fellahs ever read
this fine piece of literature?

11:55.347 --> 11:57.983
{\an3}- "Horrible Wolfie
the Harmless Wolfpup?"

11:58.050 --> 12:00.820
- Yes, it's the touching story
of a kid wolf

12:00.886 --> 12:02.521
<i>who shows up</i>
<i>at a town full of humans</i>

12:02.588 --> 12:04.857
<i>who all want to run</i>
<i>him through with a pitchfork.</i>

12:04.924 --> 12:06.826
<i>- That's supposed</i>
<i>to be touching?</i>

12:06.892 --> 12:08.561
<i>- But Wolfie didn't run away.</i>

12:08.627 --> 12:11.764
<i>He performed loving deeds</i>
<i>for the hateful townfolk,</i>

12:11.831 --> 12:14.066
<i>and they welcomed</i>
<i>him into their hearts!</i>

12:14.133 --> 12:16.635
So that's what we'll do.
We'll get in our giant tank

12:16.702 --> 12:18.804
and smash people in the face
with good deeds!

12:18.871 --> 12:21.140
{\an1}- Yeah!
We are good-doers!

12:21.207 --> 12:24.343
{\an3}- Oh, this is gonna look great
on my college application!

12:24.410 --> 12:27.847
- Any votes for staying home
during the anti-mutant panic?

12:27.913 --> 12:30.483
No?
Okay, leggo!

12:30.549 --> 12:33.352
- Now each time
we do a good deed,

12:33.419 --> 12:36.422
we'll leave behind one of
our friendly calling cards.

12:36.489 --> 12:40.493
{\an3}- This good deed brought to you
by the "Mutant Menace."

12:40.559 --> 12:44.563
Winky face!
Who wouldn't love this?

12:44.630 --> 12:46.465
[tires screech]

12:46.532 --> 12:48.734
- Uh-huh, mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

12:48.801 --> 12:51.737
<i>[funky music]</i>

12:51.804 --> 12:57.076
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:57.143 --> 12:59.378
- [meowing]

12:59.445 --> 13:02.915
- Aww, kitty need to go inside?

13:10.589 --> 13:12.358
[vacuum whirring]

13:19.098 --> 13:21.300
- [groans]

13:21.367 --> 13:24.637
- Boys, we're good-doers.
And what do good-doers do?

13:24.703 --> 13:27.973
They good-do,
and they good-do it well!

13:28.040 --> 13:30.976
{\an3}- New York is going
to adore us.

13:31.043 --> 13:33.846
<i>- In local news,</i>
<i>a team of heartless pranksters</i>

13:33.913 --> 13:37.883
<i>dubbed the "Mutant Menace</i>
<i>Evil Winky Face"</i>

13:37.950 --> 13:40.753
<i>are wreaking havoc</i>
<i>across the city.</i>

13:40.819 --> 13:44.690
<i>We go live to unpaid</i>
<i>E-reporter, Cybersleuth.</i>

13:44.757 --> 13:46.759
{\an8}<i>- A fire rages.</i>

13:46.825 --> 13:48.794
{\an8}<i>[clamoring]</i>

13:48.861 --> 13:51.730
{\an8}<i>A canary flees for its life.</i>

13:51.797 --> 13:54.366
{\an8}<i>A Maltese is trapped</i>
<i>in concrete.</i>

13:54.433 --> 13:57.069
{\an8}<i>What do these tragedies</i>
<i>have in common?</i>

13:57.136 --> 14:01.340
{\an8}<i>The horrible villains</i>
<i>called the Mutant Menace!</i>

14:01.407 --> 14:02.875
{\an1}- What?

14:02.942 --> 14:05.911
{\an1}We called ourselves
the Mutant Menace as a joke!

14:05.978 --> 14:07.112
That's why we used the
"just-kidding" quotes,

14:07.179 --> 14:08.881
and the
just-kidding winky face!

14:08.948 --> 14:11.350
{\an1}- Raph, you know I love you,
but people don't focus

14:11.417 --> 14:14.086
{\an1}on punctuation
when they're stuck in concrete.

14:14.153 --> 14:17.389
- There's something familiar
about that disguised voice.

14:17.456 --> 14:19.558
<i>- No doubt you're wondering</i>
<i>who I am.</i>

14:19.625 --> 14:25.164
<i>I am none other than</i>
<i>boy genius Baxter Stockboy!</i>

14:25.231 --> 14:28.000
- What?
both: Baxter Stockboy!

14:28.067 --> 14:30.970
{\an1}- I am not looking forward
to whatever that highly-skilled

14:31.036 --> 14:33.038
{\an1}under-achiever
has in store for us.

14:33.105 --> 14:35.374
<i>- Never fear, New York.</i>

14:35.441 --> 14:38.410
<i>I will expose these monsters</i>
<i>for what they are!</i>

14:38.477 --> 14:41.847
<i>I have been tracking them</i>
<i>from the Stock-N-Shop Blimp.</i>

14:41.914 --> 14:43.649
- He's tracking us?

14:43.716 --> 14:45.618
- Hey, we look like
a giant turtle!

14:45.684 --> 14:48.153
{\an3}- Yeah, everybody was saying
"go stealth, go stealth."

14:48.220 --> 14:50.856
{\an3}But come on, look at us.
We all kinds of bad!

14:50.923 --> 14:52.992
<i>- You, too, can track</i>
<i>the mutant menace</i>

14:53.058 --> 14:57.029
<i>by accessing the</i>
<i>Baxter Stockboy Live Stream,</i>

14:57.096 --> 14:59.365
<i>available for</i>
<i>a reasonable fee.</i>

14:59.431 --> 15:01.033
- We can't let anyone see us.

15:01.100 --> 15:04.203
{\an1}We need to get home
<i>muy rapido.</i>

15:04.270 --> 15:05.604
<i>[engine revving]</i>

15:05.671 --> 15:07.239
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

15:07.306 --> 15:08.407
- What the--

15:08.474 --> 15:09.642
[clamoring]

15:09.708 --> 15:11.310
[tires screech]

15:11.377 --> 15:14.847
- It's them!
The Mutant Menace!

15:14.913 --> 15:16.348
- Get them!

15:16.415 --> 15:17.783
{\an3}- You know, you don't
normally see pitchforks

15:17.850 --> 15:19.251
in Mid-Town Manhattan.

15:19.318 --> 15:22.254
{\an1}- Oh, mama, people are
getting rustic out there!

15:22.321 --> 15:23.822
- We were trying
to be nice to them.

15:23.889 --> 15:26.125
Have they never read
"Horrible Wolfie?"

15:26.191 --> 15:28.260
- Ah, force shields down 50%.

15:28.327 --> 15:30.429
- Wait a second,
we have force shields?

15:30.496 --> 15:32.331
- We do not.

15:32.398 --> 15:34.099
- You shall not pass!

15:34.166 --> 15:35.801
- [yelps]

15:35.868 --> 15:37.369
- [groans]

15:37.436 --> 15:40.372
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

15:40.439 --> 15:43.909
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:43.976 --> 15:46.812
<i>[beeping]</i>

15:58.490 --> 16:00.059
[yelping]

16:02.695 --> 16:04.229
- Oh, Raph-a-la, would you mind

16:04.296 --> 16:05.931
easing up on the gas,
dear friend?

16:05.998 --> 16:08.534
{\an3}- I can't, the throttle's stuck
or something.

16:08.600 --> 16:12.838
No brakes, no steering!
Donnie, what's going on?

16:12.905 --> 16:16.742
{\an1}- Oh, no, oh, no!
Ah, okay, whew.

16:16.809 --> 16:18.911
{\an1}Good news, guys.
My engineering is fine.

16:18.977 --> 16:21.280
{\an1}Oh, and something's taken
control of the Turtle Tank.

16:21.347 --> 16:23.048
- Look out!

16:23.115 --> 16:25.217
- I'm trying the taxi rockets!

16:25.284 --> 16:26.552
<i>[whirring]</i>

16:26.618 --> 16:28.554
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!
- Look out, et cetera!

16:28.620 --> 16:29.955
Whoa!

16:30.022 --> 16:31.890
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:38.764 --> 16:40.666
- Wow, nice work, Raph.

16:40.733 --> 16:42.568
{\an1}But we can't
keep this up forever.

16:42.634 --> 16:44.436
{\an1}Those rockets
have limited fuel.

16:44.503 --> 16:46.171
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:46.238 --> 16:47.573
- Trapped?

16:47.639 --> 16:50.309
{\an3}I knew being nice to
people would get us in trouble.

16:50.376 --> 16:52.511
[metal scraping]

16:55.547 --> 16:56.615
<i>[8-bit music]</i>

16:56.682 --> 16:58.617
- Chell-o?
- Mikey,

16:58.684 --> 17:01.520
we do not "chell-o" the enemy.

17:01.587 --> 17:05.089
<i>- Oh, mutants,</i>
<i>you no doubt have noticed</i>

17:05.156 --> 17:08.926
<i>my microbots are in control</i>
<i>of your vehicle.</i>

17:08.993 --> 17:10.829
[tires screeching]

17:10.896 --> 17:12.231
[clucking]

17:12.297 --> 17:13.298
- [yells]

17:13.365 --> 17:17.336
- What's your angle, Stockboy?

17:17.403 --> 17:19.338
- Just watch!

17:19.405 --> 17:22.508
<i>New York, I will deliver</i>
<i>the Mutant Menace</i>

17:22.574 --> 17:26.412
<i>to the steps of City Hall</i>
<i>in five minutes!</i>

17:26.478 --> 17:29.048
{\an8}<i>Subscribe and donate</i>
<i>to my live stream</i>

17:29.114 --> 17:30.983
{\an8}<i>to witness the spectacle!</i>

17:31.049 --> 17:33.585
{\an8}<i>Or see it in person,</i>
<i>if you dare.</i>

17:33.652 --> 17:35.354
<i>Premium tickets are for sale</i>
<i>on my website.</i>

17:35.421 --> 17:37.022
<i>We accept cash,</i>
<i>credit cards, cryptocurrency--</i>

17:37.089 --> 17:39.591
- What is with this kid?
He's going to expose us

17:39.658 --> 17:41.260
all to New York just for money?

17:41.326 --> 17:42.761
- Yeah, we don't
have any money,

17:42.828 --> 17:44.163
and we get by just fine.

17:44.229 --> 17:45.964
- Yeah, yeah, yeah,
we are poor as dirt.

17:46.031 --> 17:46.999
[yelps]

17:47.065 --> 17:49.868
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

17:49.935 --> 17:51.837
- I can't steer
and I can't stop!

17:51.904 --> 17:53.338
[yelps]

17:53.405 --> 17:55.641
- Step aside,
it's portal time!

17:55.707 --> 17:57.643
- No!
- No, stop, no!

17:57.709 --> 18:00.345
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:00.412 --> 18:02.514
[all yelling]

18:08.887 --> 18:11.056
[all grunting]

18:11.123 --> 18:13.425
- Hey, one of Leo's portals
didn't work,

18:13.492 --> 18:15.694
we all totally expected.

18:15.761 --> 18:17.262
Oh, Newton's apple!

18:17.329 --> 18:19.531
How could I forget
the floor hatch?

18:19.598 --> 18:21.633
I can just shimmy out
and see if--

18:21.700 --> 18:23.836
- No time for that.
I'll go.

18:23.902 --> 18:27.339
[grunting]

18:27.406 --> 18:29.208
[yelps]

18:30.275 --> 18:34.346
Donnie!
Ow, ow, ow, ow, ow!

18:34.413 --> 18:36.348
Make this hatch bigger!
Ow, ow, ow!

18:36.415 --> 18:38.550
{\an3}- I made it to your specs,
but that was when

18:38.617 --> 18:41.653
{\an3}you were in your "doing
sit-ups every day" phase.

18:41.720 --> 18:43.055
[loud bump]

18:43.889 --> 18:46.425
<i>[beeping]</i>

18:46.492 --> 18:48.126
[tires screech]

18:49.394 --> 18:53.065
<i>- Three minutes to the reveal</i>
<i>of the Mutant Menace!</i>

18:53.131 --> 18:55.267
- What do we do, what do we do,
what do we do?

18:55.334 --> 18:59.037
- We send this gasbag
on the highway to helium!

19:00.339 --> 19:03.375
<i>[various beeping]</i>

19:08.947 --> 19:11.683
- Ah, now they're
shooting blimps!

19:11.750 --> 19:14.686
- The whales of the sky.

19:14.753 --> 19:16.922
- Step right up, folks!

19:16.989 --> 19:19.658
{\an1}Any moment, you can behold
the Mutant Menace,

19:19.725 --> 19:22.561
{\an1}the dangerous spectacle
that's sweeping New York!

19:22.628 --> 19:25.564
One dollar per person.
Cash preferred.

19:25.631 --> 19:28.267
- Okay, we're out of jet fuel,
we're out of bowling balls,

19:28.333 --> 19:29.902
and we're going to be
exposed to New York

19:29.968 --> 19:32.004
smelling like the inside
of this tank!

19:32.070 --> 19:34.406
- Relax, Leo.
We still have

19:34.473 --> 19:36.642
nature's bowling ball.
Me!

19:36.708 --> 19:38.477
[grunts]

19:38.544 --> 19:41.446
<i>[rock music]</i>

19:41.513 --> 19:43.315
Launch me, baby!

19:43.382 --> 19:46.852
Hot soup!

19:46.919 --> 19:49.855
Mystic whip grip!

19:49.922 --> 19:51.990
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:52.057 --> 19:53.959
- No, no, no!

19:54.026 --> 19:57.162
{\an1}- There they are!
They're right behind you!

19:58.730 --> 20:03.335
{\an1}There they are!
Turn around, turn around!

20:03.402 --> 20:05.304
all: Huh?

20:05.370 --> 20:09.141
- Hey, that's an empty street!
- Oh, come on!

20:09.207 --> 20:11.243
[clamoring]

20:14.212 --> 20:16.415
- Phew, Mikey with the save!

20:16.481 --> 20:18.550
Oh, no!

20:18.617 --> 20:22.387
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:22.454 --> 20:23.555
- [gasps]

20:26.024 --> 20:28.293
- [yells]

20:30.963 --> 20:32.598
- [yells]

20:34.800 --> 20:36.702
<i>[electricity crackling]</i>

20:42.274 --> 20:44.710
Nice one, Mike.
You see that, Raph?

20:44.776 --> 20:46.478
- [gurgling]

20:46.545 --> 20:48.380
- Um, hey, Donnie,
we're sinking

20:48.447 --> 20:50.148
and Raph is swallowing
the Hudson River.

20:50.215 --> 20:52.084
{\an3}- Do you really think
I would have built this tank

20:52.150 --> 20:54.987
without an amphibious mode?

20:55.053 --> 20:56.421
<i>[kazoo blows]</i>

20:56.488 --> 20:58.924
Oh, that is the wrong button.
Here we go.

20:58.991 --> 21:01.560
[air hisses]

21:01.627 --> 21:03.962
- [gasps]

21:04.029 --> 21:06.498
{\an1}- Dumb Stock-N-Shop
publicity stunt!

21:06.565 --> 21:07.666
- Total scam!

21:07.733 --> 21:11.036
{\an3}I spent $60 on pitchforks
for nothing!

21:11.103 --> 21:12.671
- Baxter Stockboy,
we're taking you in

21:12.738 --> 21:15.273
{\an3}for unlicensed advertising,
causing mass hysteria,

21:15.340 --> 21:18.110
{\an3}and driving a blimp
without a learner's permit.

21:18.176 --> 21:19.878
{\an3}Alright, take him
to kid genius jail.

21:19.945 --> 21:22.748
- Mark my words, this isn't
the last you've heard

21:22.814 --> 21:26.084
of Baxter Stockboy!

21:27.719 --> 21:30.255
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

21:30.322 --> 21:32.691
{\an1}- Well, I guess
we'll never get people

21:32.758 --> 21:35.260
{\an1}to accept us for
being good-doers like Wolfie.

21:35.327 --> 21:38.463
- Maybe not, Mikey,
but we'll keep trying,

21:38.530 --> 21:42.668
because we're the
"Mad Dogs," winky face!

21:42.734 --> 21:45.937
- Hey, uh, Raph, did you ever
finish reading your book here?

21:46.004 --> 21:48.573
Because turns out after
the villagers accept Wolfie

21:48.640 --> 21:50.609
into their hearts,
he eats them all.

21:50.676 --> 21:53.879
<i>- I got to start</i>
<i>reading stuff to the end.</i>

21:53.945 --> 21:56.782
<i>[upbeat rock music]</i>

21:56.848 --> 22:04.089
<i>♪ ♪</i>
